#:culture{:id "tuv.dish.pulaka", :name "Pulaka", :country "TUV", :kind :dish, :summary "Giant swamp taro (Cyrtosperma merkusii) grown mainly in Tuvalu and an important source of carbohydrates; families maintain ancestral cultivation pits and pass growing techniques through generations, though the crop now faces threats from rising sea levels.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulaka", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
#:culture{:id "tuv.dish.fekei", :name "Fekei", :country "TUV", :kind :dish, :summary "Tuvaluan dish made on all the islands, consisting of grated pulaka wrapped in pulaka leaves, steamed, and mixed with coconut cream, per the Wikipedia article on Tuvaluan cuisine.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuvaluan_cuisine", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
#:culture{:id "tuv.dish.palusami", :name "Palusami", :country "TUV", :kind :dish, :summary "Also called samoa; served with taro or breadfruit and made of taro leaves, coconut cream, lime juice, onions and spices, per the Wikipedia article on Tuvaluan cuisine, which notes the alternate name reflecting the dish's shared presence in Samoan cuisine.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuvaluan_cuisine", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
#:culture{:id "tuv.beverage.kava", :name "Kava", :country "TUV", :kind :beverage, :summary "Listed as Tuvalu's national drink in the infobox of the Wikipedia article on Tuvaluan cuisine.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuvaluan_cuisine", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
#:culture{:id "tuv.festival.fatele", :name "Fatele", :country "TUV", :kind :festival, :summary "Traditional dance song of Tuvalu, the most common form of traditional Tuvaluan musical expression; evolved from a seated performance by unmarried women into a modern standing dance performed at community events and celebrations.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatele", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
#:culture{:id "tuv.heritage.funafuti-conservation-area", :name "Funafuti Conservation Area", :country "TUV", :kind :heritage, :summary "Marine conservation area covering 33 square kilometers of reef, lagoon and motu (islets) on the western side of Funafuti atoll, established in 1999 and encompassing about one-fifth of the coral reef area of Funafuti lagoon.", :url "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funafuti_Conservation_Area", :url-provenance :wikipedia-en, :retrieved-at "2026-07-17"}
